
This correction method is detailed in:
    Biktagirov, et al., "Spin decontamination for magnetic dipolar coupling calculations: Application to high-spin molecules and solid-state spin qubits", Phys. Rev. Research 2, 022024(R) (2020)


Steps:

(1) Run pw.x in each of NV, C1, C2, and C3

(2) Move the Run_PyZFS.py file into the "out" folder.

(3) Compute ZFS by running "mpirun python Run_PyZFS.py > ZFS_OutFile.txt".
    Make sure to save the output into the ZFS_OutFile.txt file.

(4) Run "python Get_ZFS_WithCorr.py".



You should get roughly the following output:

Uncorrected ZFS:    3047 GHz
Corrected ZFS:      2561 GHz

